Ethical Issues
 Project Ethics for Development and Use
Data minimalization
•	Risk (low): Currently the application will only have access to user credentials for log in, user scans, and the cards in the collection which represent the total available cards the application is trained to identify. Data usage concerns regarding the ethicality of the model is low, image identification models have been trained far before the existence of emergent data centers and the technology shows no significant ethical concern in its data usage. It also is trained on an open source community supported API so no images or data was acquired without the express permission of users whose content was posted for the purpose of free and fair use. Supabase will handle the vast majority of data storage. While cloud servers pose a potential ethical concern, the environmental or social impact is overall lower than an in-house hosted server.
•	Prevention: No discernible action can be taken to mitigate this risk.

Legal Issues
 Project Legality
Copyright
•	Risk(Critical): The Pokémon artwork and images belong to the Pokémon company, using open source API’s based on their legal trademark could potentially lead to breach of copyright or other legal ramifications.
•	Prevention: The best method of prevention is to avoid any official publicly available release of the application in order to avoid potential legal ramifications.
Legal containment of user data
•	Risk(medium): User Data, regardless of sensitivity, is in certain cases a legal right, such as data privacy laws in California and Great Britain which protects user access to their own data.
•	Prevention: Best practice is to allow users the powers to access their data and provide a path by which any user may request to have their data sent to them or deleted.
Inaccurate trade data
•	Risk(low): If trade data is misleading or fraudulent, it could entice users into participating in fraudulent transactions. Though the application does not feature a trade platform and bears no responsibility for use of the data provided (which is provided by third party API’s), there could be certain situations in which the app could be civilly liable for inaccurate trades.
•	Prevention: insert disclaimer of potential inaccurate information and provide citation for data sources in the application. Unfortunately however, as the data used to inform on the trade data does not belong to us, we have no power to change it ourselves and so no further prevention methods will be employed currently.
